README

1. To compile alloc_anon_memory.c invoke
   $ gcc alloc_anon_memory.c -o alloc_anon_memory.exe

2. To compile uevent_listener.c invoke
   $ gcc -Wall -g -o uevent_listener.exe uevent_listener.c -ludev

   - When running ./uevent_listener.c please run it with sudo permissions, so
     that the program has permissions to write the new configurations

   - Tutorial for using udevmonitor and sysfs when writing uevent_listener.c
     described in:
     http://www.signal11.us/oss/udev/
